<br>
1.)  Control your aggro.<br>
<br>
   If you are a wizard/nuker, and not expected to mana burn, your role in the  group should mean not getting aggro. Wait until that mob is at 50% or whatever before you toss out that ice comet. Have that wizzy concussion thing scribed and ready to go if you own it.<br>
<br>
2.) If you cast high aggro spells - mez/slow /etc.cast only if it is really, needed. If your party of 30 raids, and can t split 2 50 mobs on the way up - the raid probably shouldn t be there..<br>
<br>
If the mob is unmezzable/slowable - don't try -you will probably be summoned and die....  If you are resisted a lot because of level/high mr mob - only attempt to mez if it is really necessary to achieve your goal.<br>
<br>
Have a mem blur or atone up if all else fails - erase their aggro list...<br>
<br>
If you are a healer. An add will aggro ch all of the time at the big boy levels. sorry it's the truth. If you are in a ch rotation, you have no choice, hopefully your rotation is a single level 66 mob encounter...<br>
<br>
I'm not gonna tell ya how to play your toon. there is a time for heal over times and a time for ch. Just know which one causes more aggro. Atone if you need too - and have that DA up.<br>
<br>
Ideally only the main tank or tanks if there is a split should have aggro. Wait until the big guys (60+ warriors, sks) aggro before sending in your 46 ranger to get a piece of the action.<br>
<br>
3.) Stay out of a pathing mob's path if you are waiting for directions, etc. Usually this is up against a wall.<br>
<br>
4.) Do what your raid leader says.<br>
5.) Some mobs see through invis on corpse runs -always check with the raid leader before you venture anywhere... <p>I never said I wasn't crazy.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ursimajor1>UrsiMajor1</A> at: 7/3/03 6:35 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub135.ezboard.com/bexodusfellowshipforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=berina759>Berina759</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#A8A8A8>(7/2/03 10:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub135.ezboard.com/fexodusfellowshipforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1522.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How to kick the bucket less on raids</span><hr size=1> Good points Ursi    I know how to kick the bucket less on raids!   DON't go on them if you don't want to die!   No safe raids ever, when I go on them i expect to die unless of course I am in Ursi's group.......hehehe<br>
